Dog Trainer Questionnaire vs Status (W, AD, GD)

Marinara Marcato

Introduction

This document tests the hypothesis that there is a difference in behaviours reported in the standardised questionnaire Monash Canine Personality Questionnaire - Revised considering dogs training outcome status.

Data Exploration

Data Analysis

Kruskal-Wallis test was used to investigate whether there was a statistically significant difference between the behaviours reported by trainers and the training outcome status of the dogs. The variables that showed p_value < 0.05 are below:

##                  Variable status_p
## 1     Extraversion.Active   0.0388
## 2  Extraversion.Energetic   0.0076
## 3     Extraversion.Lively   0.0189
## 4  Motivation.Persevering   0.0106
## 5       Training.Reliable   0.0015
## 6      Training.Trainable   0.0002
## 7  Amicability.Easy.going   0.0025
## 8    Amicability.Friendly   0.0136
## 9     Amicability.Relaxed   0.0032
## 10   Amicability.Sociable   0.0433
## 11    Neuroticism.Fearful   0.0016
## 12    Neuroticism.Nervous   0.0050
## 13      Neuroticism.Timid   0.0207
